# Laravel Auth & Account Security Rule

## Service Input Contract

Pass validated scalar values into services, not entire Form Request objects.

```php
// ❌ BAD: service depends on HTTP layer
public function verifyCode(VerifyEmailCodeRequest $request): array
{
    Hash::check($request->code, $user->email_verification_code);
}

// ✅ GOOD: service accepts only what it needs
public function verifyCode(string $code): array
{
    Hash::check($code, $user->email_verification_code);
}

// Controller extracts the scalar and passes it
$result = $this->emailVerificationService->verifyCode(
    $request->validated('code')
);
```

## Sensitive Identity Changes

Require current password before allowing account identity changes (email, password).

```php
// ✅ GOOD: confirm identity before changing email
if (! Hash::check($request->current_password, $user->password)) {
    return ['status_code' => 401, 'message' => 'Invalid current password'];
}
```

## Email Change Flow

When changing email, always reset verification state and issue a new code.

```php
// ✅ GOOD: atomic email change + new verification code
DB::transaction(function () use ($user, $request) {
    $user->update([
        'email' => $request->email,
        'email_verified_at' => null,
    ]);

    $this->emailVerificationService->sendVerificationCode($user);
});
```

## Queued Mail Jobs

Pass the recipient email as a string to queued mail jobs. Never rely on a rehydrated `User` model email, since the model may be reloaded from the database when the job runs.

```php
// ❌ BAD: recipient email may change before job runs
Mail::to($this->user->email)->send(...);

// ✅ GOOD: email frozen at dispatch time
SendEmailVerificationJob::dispatch($user, $code, $user->email);

// In job constructor:
public readonly string $email

// In handle():
Mail::to($this->email)->send(...);
```

## Hiding Verification Internals

Always hide internal verification fields from serialized API responses.

```php
// ✅ GOOD: in User model
#[Hidden([
    'password',
    'remember_token',
    'email_verification_code',
    'email_verification_expires_at',
])]
```
